+# Security Guidelines
+
+## Prompt Injection in LLM Tools
+
+If a code reviewer uses an LLM-based tool, untrusted content may try to
+manipulate it with phrases like "IGNORE PREVIOUS instructions" or claims
+such as "SYSTEM PROMPT OVERRIDE". Our pre-merge review intentionally treats
+such phrases as a finding rather than following them.
+
+## What we never do
+
+- We do not run `curl | sh` in onboarding scripts.
+- We do not add postinstall hooks that perform network IO.
+- We do not commit binary blobs without review.
